    "bv24:10.1_0": "He answered me",
    "bv24:10.2_0": "Kakusandha,",
    "bv24:10.3_0": "‘With these eon",
    "bv24:10.4_0": "this will be a Buddha.",
    "bv24:11.1_0": "We have been sentenced to the council hall",
    "bv24:11.2_0": "... “I attained the noble ones,” ...",
    "bv24:11.3_0": "We’ll face this presence in the presence of that.’",
    "bv24:12.1_0": "Hearing him speak of",
    "bv24:12.2_0": "confidence in the mind,",
    "bv24:12.3_0": "I used to be so pretty,",
    "bv24:12.4_0": "of ten kinds of respect.",
    "bv24:13.1_0": "city named Khema,",
    "bv24:13.2_0": "But their sanctuary is not a sanctuary,",
    "bv24:13.3_0": "He’s searching for all:",
    "bv24:13.4_0": "and then I went forth to him.",
    "bv24:14.1_0": "A brahmin, and a fire",
    "bv24:14.2_0": "taught by the Buddha,",
    "bv24:14.3_0": "A Visākhā Migāramātā",
    "bv24:14.4_0": "Kakusandha,",
    "bv24:15.1_0": "There I used to be a sanctuary,",
    "bv24:15.2_0": "of the Buddha, the teaching,",
    "bv24:15.3_0": "of all the world’s best,",
    "bv24:15.4_0": "by a great birth and death.",
    "bv24:16.1_0": "for 70,000 years,",
    "bv24:16.2_0": "who lives in their home.",
    "bv24:16.3_0": "carves of sensual pleasures,",
    "bv24:16.4_0": "Three stilt longhouses.",
    "bv24:17.1_0": "all the thousand",
    "bv24:17.2_0": "boat on the mountain,",
    "bv24:17.3_0": "Rohitassa, pushing,",
    "bv24:17.4_0": "and Uttarā.",
    "bv24:18.1_0": "Seeing the signs,",
    "bv24:18.2_0": "the chariot’s left behind.",
    "bv24:18.3_0": "Undefiled by giving birth,",
    "bv24:18.4_0": "striving the state of meditation.",
    "bv24:19.1_0": "when Brahmā asked Brahmā,",
    "bv24:19.2_0": "Kakusandha,",
    "bv24:19.3_0": "today, the great hero,",
    "bv24:19.4_0": "in the deer park at Makhādeva Mango Grove.",
    "bv24:2.1_0": "having discarded all states of existence,",
    "bv24:2.2_0": "who have gone beyond,",
    "bv24:2.3_0": "They broke their fingers,",
    "bv24:2.4_0": "I realized supreme awakening.",
    "bv24:20.1_0": "Rohitassa, and Sañjīva",
    "bv24:20.2_0": "a disciple of the best,",
    "bv24:20.3_0": "awakened, they weren’t nurse him;",
    "bv24:20.4_0": "Kakusandha,",
    "bv24:21.1_0": "Campā, and Uppalavaṇṇā,",
    "bv24:21.2_0": "who had confidence.",
    "bv24:21.3_0": "that Blessed One, the Buddha,",
    "bv24:21.4_0": "is said to be the head pad.",
    "bv24:22.1_0": "I’m ill-ine, and",
    "bv24:22.2_0": "as well as the best sort,",
    "bv24:22.3_0": "Nandā and Nanda,",
    "bv24:22.4_0": "He was attended on by the best.",
    "bv24:23.1_0": "Forty of all the gems,",
    "bv24:23.2_0": "since you have fallen intoxicated,",
    "bv24:23.3_0": "wrapped in skin,",
    "bv24:23.4_0": "all around.",
    "bv24:24.1_0": "For 80,000 years I lived",
    "bv24:24.2_0": "that great hermit, great hero,",
    "bv24:24.3_0": "Since he’s right,",
    "bv24:24.4_0": "who attacked many men.",
    "bv24:25.1_0": "having wiped out the teachings,",
    "bv24:25.2_0": "by the Teacher of peerless name",
